McQueen senior Alice Duan fired a 73 Monday at Hidden Valley for the lowest score after the first day of the girls Northern Nevada Division I golf Regional tournament. 
Abbi Fleiner, a freshman at Reno shot a 78 and Jax Sohl of Bishop Manogue is in third with an 80. 
Spanish Springs leads the team scoring with a 353, followed by McQueen at 356, Reno at 357 and Bishop Manogue at 374. 
The two-day tournament concludes Tuesday at Somersett Country Club. The first group tees off at 9 a.m. Tuesday. The leaders tee off at 11:20 a.m. 
In Division III, Kennedy Kohn of Incline is the first-day leader with a 93 at the 5,359-yard, par-72, White Pine County Golf Course in Ely. 
Sarah Isaacs of Wendover is second at 94 and Kaitlyn Alton of Wells is third at 97. 
Incline leads the team standings with a 395, followed by Wendover at 468 and Battle Mountain at 490. 
The tournament concludes Tuesday.
